The paper deals with algorithms for solving linear systems, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The focus is on Laplacian matrices, which are commonly used in graph theory (cs.DS, cs.CG). The paper also introduces a new structural result related to sparse LU factorizations, which is a topic in linear algebra (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses applications to various properties of random walks on directed graphs, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
